    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - INSTALL - SHIFTER HOUSING ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the shift bars are in the neutral position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the sliding clutches on the mainshaft in the neutral position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the shifter housing on the transmission, fitting the yokes into the yoke slots of
                the corresponding clutch gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024h7">Figure 177</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024h7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024h7" filename="../figg13/g13024h7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 177. Install Shifter Housing on Transmission</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the attaching bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
